  <h2>When to use this pattern</h2>
  <p>If you are collecting personal data in your service you should follow this pattern.</p>
  <p>Use this pattern to help users:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>consent to your service collecting personal data</li>
    <li>set and change their cookie preferences</li>
    <li>understand why/how cookies are being used</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>When not to use this pattern</h2>
  <p>Do not use this pattern if you are not collecting personal data in your service.</p>

  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <p>When using this pattern you need to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>ask users for consent</li>
    <li>provide information on cookies used</li>
    <li>allow users to set preferences</li>
    <li>allow users to change preferences</li>
    <li>inform users of any changes</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Ask users for consent</h3>
  <p>Use a cookie banner to ask users for consent that:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>appears the first time a service is used</li>
    <li>loads immediately with the page</li>
    <li>persists until the user updates their settings</li>
    <li>sits above the site header and users can scroll past it</li>
  </ul>

  <img class="app-image--border app-example--image" src="/assets/cookie-banner.png" alt="">

  <p>The banner includes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>a clear, accessible heading</li>
    <li>a simple explanation that we’ve set essential cookies</li>
    <li>information about analytics cookies, so users can give informed consent</li>
    <li>information about an extra, non-essential cookie used to record the user’s choice</li>
    <li>a link to our more detailed cookies information page, if the user needs it</li>
    <li>descriptive buttons of equal prominence to allow users to make a quick, unbiased choice</li>
  </ul>

  <img class="app-image--border app-example--image" src="/assets/cookie-banner-anatomy.png" alt="">

  <p>When users update their settings using the cookie banner, use a confirmation banner to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>confirm the users choice</li>
    <li>let users know they can change their settings</li>
    <li>link to the cookies information page</li>
  </ul>

  <img class="app-image--border app-example--image" src="/assets/cookie-banner-confirm.png" alt="">

  <h3>Provide information on cookies used</h3>
  <p>Let users gain a better understanding of the cookies used with a cookies information page that:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>explains clearly what cookies are</li>
    <li>explains what the cookies are used for</li>
    <li>includes a list of details about every essential cookie used</li>
    <li>includes a link to update their preferences</li>
  </ul>

  <p><a href="https://www.nhs.uk/our-policies/cookies-policy/">See the NHS websites cookies information page</a></p>

  <h3>Allow users to set preferences</h3>
  <p>Let users...</p>
  <p><a href="https://www.nhs.uk/our-policies/cookies-policy/cookie-settings/">See the NHS websites cookie settings page</a></p>

  <h3>Inform users of any changes</h3>
  <p>After users save their settings, use a confirmation page to tell users:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>their settings have been saved</li>
    <li>how long their settings have been saved for</li>
    <li>they can change their settings at any time (with a link to the cookies information page)</li>
  </ul>

  <img class="app-image--border app-example--image" src="/assets/cookie-saved.png" alt="">

  <h3>Allow users to change preferences</h3>
  <p>Include a cookies link in the footer so users can access the cookies information page from every page in the service.</p>

  <img class="app-image--border app-example--image" src="/assets/cookie-footer-anatomy.png" alt="">

